item.description: https://www.politico.com/news/2025/12/19/epstein-documents-release-friday-deadline-00699935 The law that was passed had no enforcement mechanism built in, no penalty for not releasing the documents or for delaying, no way to hold the executive branch accountable for failing to execute the law. Which is why the executive branch is called the executive branch - congress passes the laws as the legislative branch, and the executive branch is supposed to put those laws into action, while the judicial branch interprets the laws and decides when the laws have been broken. Currently the executive branch under Trump is trying to remake laws with executive orders and say when laws have been broken while ignoring the other two branches of government.

Our family does Xmas on the weekend before. So that's tomorrow. I'm going to head out shopping to get my wife and son something tomorrow. I don't know what yet. Something. TBH I just want to crawl into a hole ? and hibernate for the next four years. Ive been bedrotting and sleeping too much. I might be a wee bit depressed.
